The City of Tshwane has confirmed that an investigation will be conducted after a Tshwane Bus Service (TBS) caught fire and burned to ashes in Centurion, Pretoria. The bus was travelling from the East to Danville, Pretoria CBD when it caught fire. According to the bus driver, he only noticed a smoke coming from the rear and front of the bus. He immediately stopped the bus at the Centurion departure point that is situated on Pretorius Street, between Thabo Sehume and Paul Kruger Streets. The bus did not have any passengers on board and the driver did not sustain any injuries. He was, however, taken to the Bouganville Hospital for treatment of shock and smoke inhalation. The exact cause of the fire is not yet known and an investigation will be conducted by the Tshwane Metro Police Department as well as the TBS to determine the cause. -TNA Reporter Â 